BOX + Database (Left side)
External systems where raw data comes from.

UCTS Task (Ingestion Layer)
Pulls data from BOX/DB and brings it into AWS.

Integration / Processing Blocks (Middle)
These components clean, validate, transform, and route the data.

VPC with Public + Private Subnets (Center)

Public subnet has the Application Load Balancer (ALB).

Private subnets run internal application services such as VCP, CCD, DMP, SAM.

Application Services (Inside Private Subnets)
These are your microservices or backend components that handle business logic.

Cache Layer (Right side)
A high-speed in-memory cache for faster performance.

Databricks (Far Right)
Downstream analytics system that receives processed data.

CI/CD Pipeline (Bottom)
Automatically builds and deploys your code.

Containerization (Bottom Right)

ECR stores the container (Docker) images.
ECS or similar service runs those containers inside private subnets.

1. Code Pipeline (CI/CD) â€“ Builds the Container
Code Commit / Source Build Stage Deploy Stage
Take the source code, Build a Docker image
Push that image to Amazon ECR
Deploy the updated container to your application runtime (ECS)
This is automated deployment.
